dct_title_s: Glen V. Mills directory maps of Ann Arbor, Ypsilanti, and Washtenaw County 1894
dct_alternative_sm: Glen V. Mills' directory maps of Ann Arbor, Ypsilanti, and Washtenaw county 1894.
dct_description_sm: Glen V. Mills published a directories for towns and cities across Michigan in the 1890s and early 1900s. Presumably these maps would serve as an accompaniment to the directories.
Includes full page maps of Ann Arbor, Ypsilanti, and Washtenaw county. Smaller maps of surrounding cities are included on the last page of the atlas.
The maps of the cities include streets names and railroad lines. The Washtenaw county map shows plats and city and town boundaries.
dct_rights_sm: This map is in the public domain.
